          <strong><a href="https://www.discovernorthernireland.com/things-to-do/narrow-water-castle-p675101" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-mcgennis-navy hover:text-mcgennis-gold transition-colors underline">Narrow Water Castle</a></strong>, a 16th-century tower house on Carlingford Lough, represents a later chapter in the story. Built long after the height of Mag Aonghusa power, it shows the evolution of defensive architecture in Ireland and the changing nature of territorial control.
